# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Broken Flagon — .gitignore
# Tells git which files to NOT track. Keeps the repo to source files only.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
*.sublime-*

# Node / build tooling (only relevant if you add a build step later)
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
dist/
build/

# Local tooling config — machine-specific, not source.
.claude/

# Environment & secrets — never commit these. (Matters once you add the
# future hosted-server work with API keys / tokens.)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Logs and temp
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
*.orig

# Large/binary working files you usually don't want in source control.
# NOTE: if your sprite PNGs and audio ARE part of the game and you want them
# versioned (recommended for a game), DELETE the lines below so git tracks them.
# They're commented out by default so nothing is accidentally excluded — review
# and uncomment only what you deliberately want git to ignore.
# *.psd
# *.aseprite
# *.wav
# *_raw/

# The dev-only bot controller is part of the project and SHOULD be tracked,
# so it is intentionally NOT ignored here. It's inert without window.__DEV_BOT__.

# Exported bot data (overnight run CSVs) — generated output, not source.
flagon-bot-runs-*.csv
